message: "If you use B.I.O.M.A. in your research or product, please cite it as below."
title: "B.I.O.M.A.: a local efficiency-and-security micro-kernel for LLM applications"
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: "Cordeiro"
    given-names: "Jonathas Silva"
    email: "jonathas.cordeiro2023@gmail.com"
version: "1.0.0"
date-released: "2026-07-16"
license: "LicenseRef-FSL-1.1-MIT"
repository-code: "https://github.com/jonathascordeiro20/bioma-framework"
url: "https://pypi.org/project/bioma-framework/"
keywords:
  - large language models
  - context management
  - prompt compression
  - token optimization
  - context apoptosis
  - llm security
  - rust
abstract: >-
  B.I.O.M.A. is a drop-in micro-kernel (Rust + Python) that dehydrates stale,
  low-value LLM context before dispatch (class-aware half-life decay, ~1 µs
  decision latency), detects cognitive-DDoS floods, and redacts pixel-level
  secrets — with a deterministic per-request audit trail. Benchmarks with raw
  data cover an end-to-end A/B against a real coding agent and a head-to-head
  against LLMLingua-2 at matched compression budgets.
